984.name: 2594 (Super Duplex)
984.Applications: Welding austenitic-ferritic, stainless alloys of the 25% Cr, 7% Ni, 4% Mo, low C types. Welding wrought, forged or cast super duplex stainless steels for service in the as-welded Condition. Heterogeneous welding between super duplex stainless steels and dissimilar welds between other stainless and mild or low alloyed steels. The alloy is widely used in applications in which corrosion resistance is of the utmost importance. The pulp & paper industry, offshore and gas industry are areas of interest.
